      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Georg Leyh (1877-1968) was a German librarian and scholar in library science.  He worked at the university libraries 
	  of Gottingen, Konigsberg and Berlin and then in 1915 became Chief Librarian of Breslau.  After serving in the military during 
	  World War II he joined the University of Tubingen as Director of the Library in 1920, a position he held until his retirement 
	  in 1947.  He also taught in the library school there.  Leyh is considered an important figure in the field of library science 
	  and library history.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Georg Leyh Collection</emph> includes correspondence, original typed manuscripts, clippings, 
		 newspaper articles and photographs.</p></scopecontent>
      
